author: glyph
commit_message:
Merge iri-5388-4: new, internationalizable URL

Author: glyph, itamar

Reviewer: jonathanj, hawkowl

Fixes: #5388
Fixes: #8063

twisted.python.url is a new abstraction for URLs, supporting RFC 3987
IRIs.

This change also replaces the guts of twisted.python.urlpath, reducing
duplication since we cannot deprecate it immediately.

author: wouter bolsterlee
commit_message:
Also accept dictionaries as query= arguments

The URL constructor and the .replace() method now sensibly handle
dictionaries passed to the query argument, instead of strictly
requiring it to be an iterable of (key, value) pairs (both of which
must be strings).

Examples:

  URL(query={"foo": "bar"})
  url.replace(query={"foo": "bar"})

This simplifies the API for the common use case, in which:

- the order of the items does not matter
  (though Python >= 3.6 preserves dictionary order)
- no duplicate parameters are present

Updated the docs to include an example of this.

Fixes #50.

commit_message: add 'encode_stray_percents', a new argument to _percent_decode(), its variants, and URL.normalize(). This option (disabled by default, and enabled for normalize), exists to turn unmatched % characters to their encoded equivalent, correcting an otherwise improperly encoded URL. Major browsers don't do this by default, so it's currently limited to the explicit normalize step. Fixes #61.

author: Tom Most
commit_message:
Don't force encode +

Before:

>>> URL(scheme='https', host='foo', query={'f+o o': 'b+a r'}).to_text()
'https://foo/?f%2Bo o=b%2Ba r'

After:

>>> URL(scheme='https', host='foo', query={'f+o o': 'b+a r'}).to_text()
'https://foo/?f+o o=b+a r'

If spaces pass unencoded, surely + can.
